== Oldest Remains ==
[[File:有岡城の総構石垣遺構の一部.jpg|thumb|Part of the "Sōgamae" stone wall remains of [[Arioka Castle]]]]

The oldest known "Sōgamae" remains are those of [[Arioka Castle]] (Itami Castle) in [[Itami, Hyogo]], designated as a National Historic Site in 1979.<ref>‘Illustrated Medieval Castle Dictionary, Volume 3,’ p.36</ref> Originally built by the [[Itami clan]] during the [[Nanboku-chō period]], it was later renovated into a "Sōgamae" by [[Araki Murashige]] during the [[Tenshō era]], and renamed "Arioka Castle." However, the castle was abandoned after just a decade.

Additionally, the [[Yamashina Honganji]], built starting in 1483, featured a grand "Sōgamae" that surrounded its temple town with massive embankments and moats. {{refnest|group=Note|The Yamashina Honganji had three concentric outer enclosures, forming a centripetal structure around the Honganji temple.<ref>[[#Fukushima2003|Fukushima 2003]], p. 327.</ref>}}
<gallery>
File:Itamij4.jpg|A drawing of Itami during the Bunroku era
File:伊丹郷町の範囲.png|Modern map of Itami City showing the extent of the "Sōgamae"
</gallery>
{{-}}

